Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the AI Engineer position with Highmark Health. I bring over three years of professional experience in developing intelligent systems, large language models (LLMs), and AI agents, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and deployed production-grade AI solutions that directly reflect the technical foundation in software engineering and large language models this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent system with autonomous decision-making using LangChain, AutoGPT, and Semantic Kernel, enabling automated customer actions across 1,000+ endpoints. To ensure operational stability, I implemented MLOps principles by building an observability layer with LangSmith to monitor generative AI models, track agentic systems quality, and optimize model deployment for high-throughput, low-latency environments — reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built intelligent systems including a support chatbot utilizing LangChain, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and Knowledge graphs to ground generative models with external knowledge sources, reducing ticket resolution time by 20%. I also designed and deployed the software infrastructure and data pipelines for a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python and Google Cloud Platform, giving me deep experience with scalable data and ML pipelines. Together, these roles have prepared me to architect agentic systems with autonomous decision-making capabilities and integrate generative AI into existing products.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in generative techniques and model fine-tuning — skills that translate directly into the focus on continuous learning, excellent communication, and transformational leadership this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted experimentation with diffusion models and generative AI architectures using Python and PyTorch, managing the full model pipeline from training data prep to deployment using vLLM for low-latency inference. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on developing agentic frameworks and autonomous systems with LangChain and LangGraph for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex architectures clearly, mirroring the communication and collaboration skills required to develop intelligent systems in a cross-functional environment. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Highmark Health and its mission to free people to be their best.

I have always been passionate about creating a remarkable health experience and placing the customer first, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Highmark Health's vision of a world where everyone embraces health. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

